sql:
SELECT date, total_vehicles
FROM aggregated_data
ORDER BY date DESC;

external_knowledge:
- Daytime of weekdays in October refers to the period between 8:00 and 18:00 from Monday to Friday in October 2023; 
- Fixed-time traffic signals are signals that operate on a fixed, predetermined cycle, unlike actuated signals that adjust their timing based on traffic conditions; 
- Average speed is a measure of the average velocity of vehicles in a given area over a period of time, while average headway is the average time between vehicles passing a point on the road; 
- Incident locations are areas where traffic incidents (e.g., accidents, roadwork) have been reported.

sql:
SELECT AVG(average_speed) AS avg_speed, AVG(average_headway) AS avg_headway
FROM aggregated_data
WHERE location_id = (SELECT location_id FROM locations WHERE location_name = 'Central Park');
